## Error Philosophy

Errors are for AI agents and developers, not end users. Every error message must be actionable.

| Quality | Example |
|---------|---------|
| Bad | `"Error: operation failed"` |
| Bad | `"Element not found"` |
| Good | `"Element not found. Run 'snapshot -i' to see available elements, then use '@e1' syntax."` |
| Good | `"Config missing 'port' field. Expected: { port: number } in ~/.config/app.json"` |

Rules:
- Include what was expected vs what was found
- Include the command or action that would fix it
- Include the file path, line number, or config key
- Never swallow errors silently. Log them. Surface them. Make them searchable.

